The paper discusses the development and validation of aerial surveillance algorithms using simulated sensor data. This involves the use of computer vision techniques for tracking and anomaly detection, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of a traffic simulator and a controller, which suggests a focus on robotics and automation (cs.RO). Additionally, the paper discusses the simulation of complex urban environments, which could fall under the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. The use of synthetic data for evaluation purposes could also fall under the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of MATLAB for the controller, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
